Work Order Dispatching Procedure

To dispatch labor for a work order activity, the following steps should be taken:

  • Step 1: Open the GIS Map WO Dispatching screen.
  • Step 2: Select the work order activity for which to dispatch labor.
  • Step 3: Click Create Crew. The Create Crew pop up window is opened.
  • Step 4: Optionally, if this crew is being created for a temporary period of time, select the Temporary check box, and then specify the date the "temporary" crew will expire in Expiration Date.
  • Step 5: Optionally, select the Show Available Only check box to only display available employees and crews that have enough remaining available hours to perform the selected WO activities.

Labor Utilization Significance

The following color codes are used to indicate labor utilization on the calendar:

  • Gray: Non-working day for the organization or no labor scheduled for this day.
  • Green: Total scheduled hours are less than total available hours, and labor utilization is less than 80%.
  • Yellow: Total scheduled hours are between 80% and 100% of total available hours.
  • Red: Total scheduled hours exceed the total available hours.

Note: Balancing the workload for work orders of Type ST (standing work order) or MEC (multiple equipment child) is not supported.

For more information, visit the Source.

```

How to Schedule a Work Order

To schedule work orders, follow these steps:

  • Step 1: Select Work > WO Planning > WO Scheduling.
  • Step 2: Specify the following information:
    • Organization: Specify the organization for which to schedule work if you use multi-organization security.
    • Schedule By: Select one of the following options:
      • Employee - Select to schedule by employee. The system displays Employee. Enter, for Employee, the Employee for whom you wish to schedule the work.
      • Trade/Department - Select to schedule by trade/department. The system displays Trade and Department. Enter, for Trade and Department, the trade and department for which you wish to schedule the work.
    • Auto Refresh: Select for the system to automatically refresh the Daily Schedule list after scheduling an activity on the calendar. If you do not select Auto Refresh, the activity will not automatically appear in the Daily Schedule list until you manually click Refresh.
  • Step 3: To schedule unscheduled work orders, select Unscheduled WOs for Dataspy in the Activities section of the form, then select a work order from the list and drag it to the day on the calendar for which to schedule it. The system creates a new work order schedule record.

For backlogged work orders, use the following approach:

  • Step 1: Select Work > WO Planning > WO Load Balancing.
  • Step 2: Input the necessary information, including:
    • Work Order Org. - Specify the organization to which the work order belongs if you use multi-organization security.
    • Selection Parameters - Enter wild cards for parameters as necessary. For example, enter E% for Trade to retrieve all work orders with trades beginning with "E".
    • Schedule Window (Days) - Specify the number of days into the future for which to calculate labor availability.
    • Sort By - Select whether to sort by Reported Date or by Scheduled Start Date.
  • Step 3: Click Process.

Note the color indicators when viewing work order comments:

  • Yellow: Total scheduled hours are between 80% and 100% of total available hours.
  • Red: Total scheduled hours exceed the total available hours.

Scheduling unscheduled or backlogged work orders and rescheduling work orders should be performed as necessary while adhering to the steps outlined above for optimal system operation.

```
